her important point, especially if the above steps aren\'t working for you. If you are already sending messages to your verified mobile numbers but somehow not having them delivered to you, then you may find your answer on Twilio\'s SMS FAQs. Make sure your target country/market and all their network providers are supported. They have pretty much made it clear who CANNOT receive a message. In India for instance, any number on the \"National Do Not Call Registry\" will not receive SMS via Twilio.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Requirements</h4>\nThere are a couple of requirements in order to use the Event Espresso SMS Reminder extension:\n<ol>\n 	<li>You must have a verified <a href=\"https://www.twilio.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Twilio</a> account (free trial or paid subscription).</li>\n 	<li>You must have the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-twilio-core/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">WP Twilio Core WordPress plugin</a> (free) installed (1.2.0+).</li>\n 	<li>You must be using woocommerce on your website .</li>\n 	<li>You must have created a Mobile Number question (text field) and made sure it appears on the registration forms.</li>\n</ol>\";s:17:\"short_description\";s:137:\"\nThe Woocommerce SMS plugin will allow you to send SMS to your Woocommerce store\'s customers to notify them about their orders\' statuses.\";s:10:\"banner_url\";s:61:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6021/banner.png\";s:15:\"card_banner_url\";s:66:\"//s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/freemius/plugins/6021/card_banner.png\";s:15:\"selling_point_0\";s:33:\"Increase your store\'s engagement.\";s:15:\"selling_point_1\";s:63:\"Satisfy your customers showing them that you are on their back.\";s:15:\"selling_point_2\";s:54:\"Provide a Top-notch reminder and notification service.\";s:11:\"screenshots\";N;s:2:\"id\";s:4:\"1594\";s:7:\"created\";s:19:\"2020-05-02 16:20:04\";s:7:\"updated\";s:19:\"2020-11-16 07:09:19\";}s:12:\"premium_slug\";s:14:\"wc-sms-